    "narrative": "The **Austin Waves** lineup for 2026-04-12 is headlined by **Gunnar Henderson**, who at an 83.29 score represents our premier play. **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive park factor boost (+16%) and a favorable matchup against Houser, making him our most reliable source of R/HR/RBI production today. Joining him in the elite tier are **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (70.87) and **Marcell Ozuna** (67.73). **Marcell Ozuna**\u2019s score is bolstered by a significant wind-out benefit (+10%), while **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** capitalizes on a high xwOBA and a generous SP_xERA of 4.45. **Miguel Vargas** and **Heliot Ramos** also offer strong value, with **Miguel Vargas** taking advantage of favorable wind conditions and **Heliot Ramos** benefiting from the same park factor that favors **Gunnar Henderson**.\n\nWe are managing significant risk today due to several high-caliber opposing arms. **Kyle Tucker** (57.75) and **Andy Pages** (44.29) are forced to face Jacob deGrom, whose presence drags down their expected efficiency despite their individual talent. Specifically, **Andy Pages** sits near the floor, and his value is suppressed further by deGrom\u2019s elite hold capability, which significantly curbs the stolen base potential we prioritize. Meanwhile, the most difficult bench decision involved **Nolan Schanuel**, who posted a solid 56.62. He was ultimately left out in favor of our outfield versatility; while **Nolan Schanuel** offers a stable floor, the optimizer opted for **Heliot Ramos** in the outfield to capitalize on the park-factor tailwinds, despite the potential volatility of the matchup. With several lineups still pending, managers must monitor **Drake Baldwin**, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, **Gunnar Henderson**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Josh Lowe**, **Jackson Merrill**, **Andy Pages**, and **Kyle Tucker** closely to ensure they remain in the favorable batting slots assumed in these projections.",
